name: Prof. Dr. John Cole
about: I'm a Professor of Instruction in the Computer Science Department here at the University of Texas at Dallas. I taught part-time at Collin County Community College for three years, and prior to that, at Illinois Institute of Technology in the mid-1970s, which is also where I earned my degrees.

name: Prof. Dr. Sanda Harabagiu
about: My research interests include Natural Language Processing, Information Retrieval, Knowledge Processing, Artificial Intelligence and more recently Medical Informatics. I have been interested for a long time in Textual Question-Answering, reference resolution and textual cohesion and coherence.

name: Prof. Dr. Ravi Prakash
about: I am a professor in the Department of Computer Science and the Collegium V Honors College at the University of Texas at Dallas. My research interests include Field-of-View prediction and caching for 360-degree videos, coexistence of wireless networks (including WiFi networks) in unlicensed and shared frequency bands, sensor networking, mobile computing and distributed algorithms.

name: Prof. Dr. Jason P. Jue
about: I am conducting research that focuses on the design and analysis of next-generation optical network architectures and protocols, including work on control and management in optical networks, protocols for multi-domain optical networks, and methods for providing survivability in optical networks.
expertise: Performance of Computer Systems and Networks

name: Prof. Dr. Nurcan Yuruk
about: I am an Associate Professor in the Department of Computer Science at University of Texas at Dallas. My research interests primarily focus on Knowledge Discovery and Data Mining and Social Network Analysis

name: Prof. Dr. Anurag Nagar
about: I am an Assistant Professor in the Department of Computer Science at the University of Texas at Dallas. My research interests primarily focus on Machine Learning, Bioinformatics and Financial Data Mining

name: Prof. Dr. Anjum Chida
about: I am an Associate Professor in the Department of Computer Science at University of Texas at Dallas. My research interests primarily focus on Machine Learning, Bioinformatics and Computational Biology

name: Prof. Dr. Yu Xiang
about: I am an Assistant Professor in the Department of Computer Science at the University of Texas at Dallas.My research interests primarily focus on robotics and computer vision. I am interested in studying how can an intelligent system or a robot understand its 3D environment from sensing and accomplish tasks in the real world, which is a very challenging and unsolved problem.
